-- Spain Sells $4.4 Billion of Treasury Bills; Yields Fall From June Auction
-- Paul Tobin
-- 2010-07-27T08:48:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-27/spain-sells-4-4-billion-of-treasury-bills-yields-fall-from-june-auction.html

          
          
             Spain sold 3.4 billion euros ($4.4
billion) of treasury bills today, the top end of the range set
for the auction, the Bank of Spain said.  
 Spain sold 971.4 million euros of 3-month bills today at an
average yield of 0.672 percent, compared with 0.913 percent at
the last sale on June 22, as demand was 5.67 times the amount
sold. It also sold 2.46 billion euros of 6-month bills at 1.144
percent, compared with 1.577 percent in June. The bid-to-cover
ratio was 2.2. The indicative range set for the offering was 2.5
billion euros to 3.5 billion euros.   
          
          


  


        